NAME
    xargs - execute command for each stdin line

SYNOPSIS
    <input> | xargs <command> [args...]

DESCRIPTION
    Reads lines from stdin and executes the specified command
    once for each line, appending the line as the last argument.

OPTIONS
    None

EXAMPLES
    find /api/data/users | xargs cat
        Display contents of each user record

    find . | grep users | xargs ls -l
        Long listing of each path containing "users"

    echo "/api/data/users" | xargs ls
        List the users directory

EXIT STATUS
    Returns the exit code of the last command executed,
    or 1 if any command failed.

SEE ALSO
    find, grep, cat
